ce:section.ce:para:
A battery test bench, as shown in Fig. 3, is established to conduct battery experiments under EV current profiles based on UDDS. The setup consists of five parts, including an Arbin BT2000 battery tester, a host computer, a high-precision rheostat, a two-pole switch and a LIB whose specification is listed in Table 2. (1) Arbin BT2000 battery tester provides the programmed current profiles and achieves the accuracy up to 0.02 V (BTS2000 has a voltage range of −10 V to 10 V with 0.1% FSR accuracy). (2) A high-precision rheostat (0–400 
   Ω
) simulates the ISC resistance with different magnitudes. (3) A two-pole switch controls the connection of the SC resistance. (4) The host computer monitors and records the measured voltage, current from the battery tester with a sample frequency of 1 Hz. The experimental conditions including fault source, fault type and fault value are summarized in Table 3.
